dsDescriptionValue.value:
This 300-item personality scale consists of adjectives to which the respondent is to respond Y if the item is descriptive of him/herself and N if it is not. Subscales include number of items to which answer was Y, number of favorable items, number of unfavorable items, communality, achievement, dominance, endurance, intraception, nurturance, affiliation, heterosexuality, exhibition, autonomy, aggression, change, succorance, abasement, deference, counseling readiness, self-control, self-confid ence, personal adjustment, ideal self, creative personality, military leader, masculine, feminine, critical parent, nurturing parent, adult, free child, adapted child, origence, and intellectence.

Scoring information. The following data step performs the necessary transformations to the thirty-seven raw scale sums of the Gough Adjective Check List. Procedures for doing the transformations are also described by Swede, l983. Three quantities necessary for the transformation were calculated separately for males and females. The mean and standard deviation of each scale were determined. The correlation of the first scale (number of adjectives checked) with each of the other scales was calculated. The appropriate male or female value for these quantities was then used to transform each respondent's rating for each scale. The respondent's raw scale value was standardized by subtracting that scale's mean and dividing by the scale's standard deviation. The variance due to the number of adjectives checked was partialled out (Nunnally, 1967) by subtracting the product of the standardized scale times the correlation of that scale with the number of adjectives checked from the standardized scale. The adjusted scale was restandardized by dividing by the square root of one minus the correlation squared (the variance remaining in the scale after the variance due to number of adjectives has been removed). this result was converted to a T-score (mean=50, standard deviation=10.0, and zero correlation with number of adjectives checked) by multiplying times ten and adding fifty. See codebook for additional information
